check  man shutdown

example:
shutdown -h  now   ==> shut down immediately

shutdown -h 20:25   ==> shut down at 20:25

shutdown -h +10  ==> shut down after 10 mins

shutdown -r now  ==> reboot now

shutdown -r +30  'message' ==> reboot 30 mins later with message

shutdown -k now 'message' ==> not shut down, only send out warning


[stian@v2stian ~]$ shutdown -k now 'message'
Must be root.



shutdown -c ==> cancel shut down